hopobject.body: I'd like to change some money anavar powder taste For his part, the Maltese hunter on the ground applied much the same logic. ‘If I don’t shoot it, someone else will, so I’d rather shoot it myself,’ one individual explained when asked why he killed as he did. The argument is revealing for drawing its primary meaning from competition among the hunters, and also for its utter lack of reference to the prey itself. It is, in truth, not a rationale for hunting. That surely requires some imaginative transaction, some ecological linkage, between the hunter and his target. To justify the killing as a means to pre-empt one’s predatory competitors is little more than a charter for the quarry’s eventual extinction.
